-- Essap to Build $516 Million of Water Plants in Paraguay
-- B y   S t e p h a n   N i e l s e n
-- 2013-09-17T18:18:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-17/essap-to-build-516-million-of-water-plants-in-paraguay.html
Paraguay’s state water utility
plans to build four sewage plants for the capital Asuncion and
the surrounding metropolitan area that will cost $516 million.  Essap, as the utility is known, is in talks with Brazilian
construction company Odebrecht SA to develop the landlocked
country’s water and water-treatment infrastructure, the
government said in a Sept. 13  statement . Essap is officially
known as Empresa de Servicios Sanitarios del Paraguay SA.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephan Nielsen in Sao Paulo at 
 snielsen8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
